{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":597,"text":"When you're a child,"},{"time":2478,"text":"anything and everything is possible."},{"time":6147,"text":"The challenge, so often,\nis hanging on to that as we grow up."},{"time":10596,"text":"And as a four-year-old,"},{"time":12181,"text":"I had the opportunity\nto sail for the first time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15671,"text":"I will never forget\nthe excitement as we closed the coast."},{"time":19878,"text":"I will never forget"},{"time":21643,"text":"the feeling of adventure\nas I climbed on board the boat"},{"time":24638,"text":"and stared into her tiny cabin\nfor the first time."},{"time":28280,"text":"But the most amazing feeling\nwas the feeling of freedom,"},{"time":31488,"text":"the feeling that I felt\nwhen we hoisted her sails."},{"time":35226,"text":"As a four-year-old child,"},{"time":37600,"text":"it was the greatest sense of freedom\nthat I could ever imagine."},{"time":41449,"text":"I made my mind up there and then\nthat one day, somehow,"},{"time":44792,"text":"I was going to sail around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48530,"text":"So I did what I could in my life\nto get closer to that dream."},{"time":52360,"text":"Age 10, it was saving my school\ndinner money change."},{"time":55426,"text":"Every single day for eight years,\nI had mashed potato and baked beans,"},{"time":59344,"text":"which cost 4p each, and gravy was free."},{"time":61997,"text":"Every day I would pile up the change\non the top of my money box,"},{"time":65014,"text":"and when that pile reached a pound,\nI would drop it in"},{"time":67604,"text":"and cross off one of the 100 squares\nI'd drawn on a piece of paper."},{"time":72167,"text":"Finally, I bought a tiny dinghy."},{"time":75418,"text":"I spent hours sitting on it in the garden\ndreaming of my goal."},{"time":79381,"text":"I read every book I could on sailing,"},{"time":82500,"text":"and then eventually,\nhaving been told by my school"},{"time":85495,"text":"I wasn't clever enough to be a vet,"},{"time":87771,"text":"left school age 17 to begin\nmy apprenticeship in sailing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92739,"text":"So imagine how it felt\njust four years later"},{"time":96830,"text":"to be sitting in a boardroom"},{"time":98506,"text":"in front of someone who I knew\ncould make that dream come true."},{"time":102895,"text":"I felt like my life\ndepended on that moment,"},{"time":106003,"text":"and incredibly, he said yes."},{"time":108644,"text":"And I could barely contain my excitement\nas I sat in that first design meeting"},{"time":112754,"text":"designing a boat\non which I was going to sail"},{"time":115564,"text":"solo nonstop around the world."},{"time":118443,"text":"From that first meeting\nto the finish line of the race,"},{"time":121299,"text":"it was everything I'd ever imagined."},{"time":123597,"text":"Just like in my dreams, there were\namazing parts and tough parts."},{"time":127498,"text":"We missed an iceberg by 20 feet."},{"time":129658,"text":"Nine times, I climbed to the top\nof her 90-foot mast."},{"time":132931,"text":"We were blown on our side\nin the Southern Ocean."},{"time":135300,"text":"But the sunsets, the wildlife,\nand the remoteness"},{"time":138272,"text":"were absolutely breathtaking."},{"time":141857,"text":"After three months at sea, age just 24,"},{"time":144504,"text":"I finished in second position."},{"time":147359,"text":"I'd loved it, so much so\nthat within six months"},{"time":150750,"text":"I decided to go around the world again,\nbut this time not in a race:"},{"time":155326,"text":"to try to be the fastest person ever\nto sail solo nonstop around the world."},{"time":160789,"text":"Now for this, I needed a different craft:"},{"time":163650,"text":"bigger, wider, faster, more powerful."},{"time":167244,"text":"Just to give that boat some scale,\nI could climb inside her mast"},{"time":170959,"text":"all the way to the top."},{"time":172863,"text":"Seventy-five foot long, 60 foot wide."},{"time":176253,"text":"I affectionately called her Moby."},{"time":178552,"text":"She was a multihull."},{"time":180311,"text":"When we built her, no one had ever\nmade it solo nonstop"},{"time":183892,"text":"around the world in one,\nthough many had tried,"},{"time":186191,"text":"but whilst we built her, a Frenchman\ntook a boat 25 percent bigger than her"},{"time":191063,"text":"and not only did he make it,\nbut he took the record from 93 days"},{"time":194852,"text":"right down to 72."},{"time":197568,"text":"The bar was now much, much higher."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200155,"text":"And these boats were exciting to sail."},{"time":202105,"text":"This was a training sail\noff the French coast."},{"time":205472,"text":"This I know well because I was one\nof the five crew members on board."},{"time":209187,"text":"Five seconds is all it took\nfrom everything being fine"},{"time":213538,"text":"to our world going black\nas the windows were thrust underwater,"},{"time":216617,"text":"and that five seconds goes quickly."},{"time":218776,"text":"Just see how far below\nthose guys the sea is."},{"time":221679,"text":"Imagine that alone\nin the Southern Ocean"},{"time":225792,"text":"plunged into icy water,\nthousands of miles away from land."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231270,"text":"It was Christmas Day."},{"time":233560,"text":"I was forging into the Southern Ocean\nunderneath Australia."},{"time":236933,"text":"The conditions were horrendous."},{"time":239550,"text":"I was approaching a part in the ocean"},{"time":241531,"text":"which was 2,000 miles away\nfrom the nearest town."},{"time":245432,"text":"The nearest land was Antarctica,\nand the nearest people"},{"time":248311,"text":"would be those manning\nthe European Space Station above me."},{"time":251180,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":252560,"text":"You really are in the middle of nowhere."},{"time":255369,"text":"If you need help,"},{"time":257180,"text":"and you're still alive,"},{"time":258736,"text":"it takes four days\nfor a ship to get to you"},{"time":261731,"text":"and then four days for that ship\nto get you back to port."},{"time":265145,"text":"No helicopter can reach you out there,"},{"time":267466,"text":"and no plane can land."},{"time":269310,"text":"We are forging ahead of a huge storm."},{"time":272944,"text":"Within it, there was 80 knots of wind,"},{"time":275370,"text":"which was far too much wind\nfor the boat and I to cope with."},{"time":278296,"text":"The waves were already 40 to 50 feet high,"},{"time":281337,"text":"and the spray from the breaking crests"},{"time":283427,"text":"was blown horizontally\nlike snow in a blizzard."},{"time":286492,"text":"If we didn't sail fast enough,\nwe'd be engulfed by that storm,"},{"time":290370,"text":"and either capsized or smashed to pieces."},{"time":293527,"text":"We were quite literally\nhanging on for our lives"},{"time":296314,"text":"and doing so on a knife edge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299518,"text":"The speed I so desperately needed\nbrought with it danger."},{"time":303351,"text":"We all know what it's like driving a car\n20 miles an hour, 30, 40."},{"time":307575,"text":"It's not too stressful.\nWe can concentrate."},{"time":310454,"text":"We can turn on the radio."},{"time":312242,"text":"Take that 50, 60, 70, accelerate through\nto 80, 90, 100 miles an hour."},{"time":316700,"text":"Now you have white knuckles\nand you're gripping the steering wheel."},{"time":319974,"text":"Now take that car off road at night"},{"time":322537,"text":"and remove the windscreen wipers,\nthe windscreen,"},{"time":324873,"text":"the headlights and the brakes."},{"time":326498,"text":"That's what it's like\nin the Southern Ocean."},{"time":328704,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":333172,"text":"You could imagine"},{"time":334041,"text":"it would be quite difficult\nto sleep in that situation,"},{"time":336831,"text":"even as a passenger."},{"time":338781,"text":"But you're not a passenger."},{"time":340306,"text":"You're alone on a boat\nyou can barely stand up in,"},{"time":342705,"text":"and you have to make\nevery single decision on board."},{"time":345213,"text":"I was absolutely exhausted,\nphysically and mentally."},{"time":348487,"text":"Eight sail changes in 12 hours."},{"time":350600,"text":"The mainsail weighed\nthree times my body weight,"},{"time":353130,"text":"and after each change,"},{"time":354827,"text":"I would collapse on the floor\nsoaked with sweat"},{"time":357124,"text":"with this freezing Southern Ocean air\nburning the back of my throat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361721,"text":"But out there, those lowest of the lows"},{"time":364276,"text":"are so often contrasted\nwith the highest of the highs."},{"time":367596,"text":"A few days later, we came out\nof the back of the low."},{"time":371659,"text":"Against all odds, we'd been able\nto drive ahead of the record"},{"time":375397,"text":"within that depression."},{"time":377464,"text":"The sky cleared, the rain stopped,"},{"time":380250,"text":"and our heartbeat, the monstrous\nseas around us were transformed"},{"time":384569,"text":"into the most beautiful moonlit mountains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388168,"text":"It's hard to explain, but you enter\na different mode when you head out there."},{"time":392765,"text":"Your boat is your entire world,"},{"time":394750,"text":"and what you take with you\nwhen you leave is all you have."},{"time":397595,"text":"If I said to you all now,\n\"Go off into Vancouver"},{"time":400612,"text":"and find everything you will need for\nyour survival for the next three months,\""},{"time":404348,"text":"that's quite a task."},{"time":406116,"text":"That's food, fuel, clothes,"},{"time":408554,"text":"even toilet roll and toothpaste."},{"time":410969,"text":"That's what we do,"},{"time":412432,"text":"and when we leave we manage it"},{"time":414336,"text":"down to the last drop of diesel\nand the last packet of food."},{"time":418000,"text":"No experience in my life"},{"time":419833,"text":"could have given me a better understanding\nof the definition of the word \"finite.\""},{"time":423740,"text":"What we have out there is all we have."},{"time":425852,"text":"There is no more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427571,"text":"And never in my life had I ever\ntranslated that definition of finite"},{"time":430891,"text":"that I'd felt on board\nto anything outside of sailing"},{"time":434211,"text":"until I stepped off the boat at\nthe finish line having broken that record."}]},{"cues":[{"time":438809,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":444265,"text":"Suddenly I connected the dots."},{"time":446935,"text":"Our global economy is no different."},{"time":449774,"text":"It's entirely dependent\non finite materials"},{"time":452276,"text":"we only have once\nin the history of humanity."},{"time":454864,"text":"And it was a bit like seeing something\nyou weren't expecting under a stone"},{"time":458638,"text":"and having two choices:"},{"time":460147,"text":"I either put that stone to one side"},{"time":462701,"text":"and learn more about it,\nor I put that stone back"},{"time":466114,"text":"and I carry on with my dream job\nof sailing around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470526,"text":"I chose the first."},{"time":472128,"text":"I put it to one side and I began\na new journey of learning,"},{"time":475611,"text":"speaking to chief executives,\nexperts, scientists, economists"},{"time":479117,"text":"to try to understand just how\nour global economy works."},{"time":482739,"text":"And my curiosity took me\nto some extraordinary places."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486431,"text":"This photo was taken in the burner\nof a coal-fired power station."},{"time":491183,"text":"I was fascinated by coal,\nfundamental to our global energy needs,"},{"time":494317,"text":"but also very close to my family."},{"time":497274,"text":"My great-grandfather was a coal miner,"},{"time":499280,"text":"and he spent 50 years\nof his life underground."},{"time":503520,"text":"This is a photo of him,\nand when you see that photo,"},{"time":506315,"text":"you see someone from another era."},{"time":508800,"text":"No one wears trousers\nwith a waistband quite that high"},{"time":511818,"text":"in this day and age. (Laughter)"},{"time":514303,"text":"But yet, that's me\nwith my great-grandfather,"},{"time":516973,"text":"and by the way, they are not\nhis real ears. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":521106,"text":"We were close. I remember sitting on\nhis knee listening to his mining stories."},{"time":525564,"text":"He talked of the camaraderie underground,"},{"time":527816,"text":"and the fact that the miners used to save\nthe crusts of their sandwiches"},{"time":531253,"text":"to give to the ponies\nthey worked with underground."},{"time":534341,"text":"It was like it was yesterday."},{"time":536732,"text":"And on my journey of learning,"},{"time":538520,"text":"I went to the World\nCoal Association website,"},{"time":540842,"text":"and there in the middle\nof the homepage, it said,"},{"time":543164,"text":"\"We have about 118 years of coal left.\""},{"time":546322,"text":"And I thought to myself, well,\nthat's well outside my lifetime,"},{"time":549456,"text":"and a much greater figure\nthan the predictions for oil."},{"time":552335,"text":"But I did the math, and I realized\nthat my great-grandfather"},{"time":555400,"text":"had been born exactly 118 years\nbefore that year,"},{"time":559974,"text":"and I sat on his knee\nuntil I was 11 years old,"},{"time":562737,"text":"and I realized it's nothing"},{"time":564641,"text":"in time, nor in history."},{"time":566963,"text":"And it made me make a decision\nI never thought I would make:"},{"time":570121,"text":"to leave the sport\nof solo sailing behind me"},{"time":572466,"text":"and focus on the greatest challenge\nI'd ever come across:"},{"time":575531,"text":"the future of our global economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577861,"text":"And I quickly realized it wasn't\njust about energy."},{"time":580570,"text":"It was also materials."},{"time":582613,"text":"In 2008, I picked up a scientific study"},{"time":584772,"text":"looking at how many years we have"},{"time":586816,"text":"of valuable materials\nto extract from the ground:"},{"time":589532,"text":"copper, 61; tin, zinc, 40; silver, 29."},{"time":593921,"text":"These figures couldn't be exact,\nbut we knew those materials were finite."},{"time":597937,"text":"We only have them once."},{"time":599674,"text":"And yet, our speed that we've used\nthese materials has increased rapidly,"},{"time":603208,"text":"exponentially."},{"time":604950,"text":"With more people in the world\nwith more stuff,"},{"time":607806,"text":"we've effectively seen\n100 years of price declines"},{"time":610580,"text":"in those basic commodities\nerased in just 10 years."},{"time":613425,"text":"And this affects all of us."},{"time":615212,"text":"It's brought huge volatility in prices,"},{"time":617232,"text":"so much so that in 2011,"},{"time":620081,"text":"your average European car manufacturer"},{"time":622619,"text":"saw a raw material price increase"},{"time":625173,"text":"of 500 million Euros,"},{"time":627379,"text":"wiping away half their operating profits"},{"time":629701,"text":"through something they have\nabsolutely no control over."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633260,"text":"And the more I learned, the more\nI started to change my own life."},{"time":636560,"text":"I started traveling less,\ndoing less, using less."},{"time":638849,"text":"It felt like actually doing less\nwas what we had to do."},{"time":642390,"text":"But it sat uneasy with me."},{"time":644740,"text":"It didn't feel right."},{"time":645862,"text":"It felt like we were\nbuying ourselves time."},{"time":648358,"text":"We were eking things out a bit longer."},{"time":650250,"text":"Even if everybody changed,\nit wouldn't solve the problem."},{"time":653477,"text":"It wouldn't fix the system."},{"time":655521,"text":"It was vital in the transition,\nbut what fascinated me was,"},{"time":658562,"text":"in the transition to what?\nWhat could actually work?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":662951,"text":"It struck me that the system itself,\nthe framework within which we live,"},{"time":667246,"text":"is fundamentally flawed,"},{"time":669545,"text":"and I realized ultimately"},{"time":672804,"text":"that our operating system,\nthe way our economy functions,"},{"time":675837,"text":"the way our economy's been built,\nis a system in itself."},{"time":679320,"text":"At sea, I had to understand\ncomplex systems."},{"time":682222,"text":"I had to take multiple inputs,"},{"time":684100,"text":"I had to process them,"},{"time":685612,"text":"and I had to understand the system to win."},{"time":688500,"text":"I had to make sense of it."},{"time":690233,"text":"And as I looked at our global economy,\nI realized it too is that system,"},{"time":694296,"text":"but it's a system that effectively\ncan't run in the long term."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698708,"text":"And I realized we've been perfecting\nwhat's effectively a linear economy"},{"time":702469,"text":"for 150 years,"},{"time":704339,"text":"where we take a material\nout of the ground,"},{"time":706370,"text":"we make something out of it,\nand then ultimately"},{"time":708878,"text":"that product gets thrown away,\nand yes, we do recycle some of it,"},{"time":712152,"text":"but more an attempt to get out\nwhat we can at the end,"},{"time":715147,"text":"not by design."},{"time":717353,"text":"It's an economy that fundamentally\ncan't run in the long term,"},{"time":720557,"text":"and if we know that we\nhave finite materials,"},{"time":723590,"text":"why would we build an economy\nthat would effectively use things up,"},{"time":726919,"text":"that would create waste?"},{"time":728777,"text":"Life itself has existed\nfor billions of years"},{"time":731702,"text":"and has continually adapted\nto use materials effectively."},{"time":735324,"text":"It's a complex system,\nbut within it, there is no waste."},{"time":738645,"text":"Everything is metabolized."},{"time":741244,"text":"It's not a linear economy\nat all, but circular."}]},{"cues":[{"time":745934,"text":"And I felt like the child in the garden."},{"time":748931,"text":"For the first time on this new journey,\nI could see exactly where we were headed."},{"time":753598,"text":"If we could build an economy that would\nuse things rather than use them up,"},{"time":757382,"text":"we could build a future that really\ncould work in the long term."},{"time":760610,"text":"I was excited."},{"time":762514,"text":"This was something to work towards."},{"time":764673,"text":"We knew exactly where we were headed.\nWe just had to work out how to get there,"},{"time":768450,"text":"and it was exactly with this in mind"},{"time":770380,"text":"that we created the Ellen MacArthur\nFoundation in September 2010."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775485,"text":"Many schools of thought fed our thinking\nand pointed to this model:"},{"time":779348,"text":"industrial symbiosis, performance economy,\nsharing economy, biomimicry,"},{"time":783968,"text":"and of course, cradle-to-cradle design."},{"time":786894,"text":"Materials would be defined\nas either technical or biological,"},{"time":790579,"text":"waste would be designed out entirely,"},{"time":793600,"text":"and we would have a system\nthat could function"},{"time":796112,"text":"absolutely in the long term."}]},{"cues":[{"time":798294,"text":"So what could this economy look like?"},{"time":801151,"text":"Maybe we wouldn't buy light fittings,\nbut we'd pay for the service of light,"},{"time":805089,"text":"and the manufacturers\nwould recover the materials"},{"time":807532,"text":"and change the light fittings\nwhen we had more efficient products."},{"time":810693,"text":"What if packaging was so nontoxic\nit could dissolve in water"},{"time":813990,"text":"and we could ultimately drink it?\nIt would never become waste."},{"time":817102,"text":"What if engines were re-manufacturable,"},{"time":819215,"text":"and we could recover\nthe component materials"},{"time":821490,"text":"and significantly reduce energy demand."},{"time":823720,"text":"What if we could recover components\nfrom circuit boards, reutilize them,"},{"time":827160,"text":"and then fundamentally recover\nthe materials within them"},{"time":829823,"text":"through a second stage?"},{"time":831225,"text":"What if we could collect\nfood waste, human waste?"},{"time":833517,"text":"What if we could turn that\ninto fertilizer, heat, energy,"},{"time":836698,"text":"ultimately reconnecting nutrients systems"},{"time":839694,"text":"and rebuilding natural capital?"},{"time":842805,"text":"And cars -- what we want\nis to move around."},{"time":845707,"text":"We don't need to own\nthe materials within them."},{"time":848350,"text":"Could cars become a service"},{"time":849989,"text":"and provide us with\nmobility in the future?"},{"time":853033,"text":"All of this sounds amazing, but these\naren't just ideas, they're real today,"},{"time":857230,"text":"and these lie at the forefront\nof the circular economy."},{"time":859950,"text":"What lies before us is to expand them\nand scale them up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864454,"text":"So how would you shift\nfrom linear to circular?"},{"time":867899,"text":"Well, the team and I at the foundation\nthought you might want to work"},{"time":871195,"text":"with the top universities in the world,"},{"time":873069,"text":"with leading businesses within the world,"},{"time":875089,"text":"with the biggest convening\nplatforms in the world,"},{"time":877437,"text":"and with governments."},{"time":878439,"text":"We thought you might want\nto work with the best analysts"},{"time":881059,"text":"and ask them the question,"},{"time":882313,"text":"\"Can the circular economy decouple\ngrowth from resource constraints?"},{"time":885514,"text":"Is the circular economy able\nto rebuild natural capital?"},{"time":889136,"text":"Could the circular economy\nreplace current chemical fertilizer use?\""},{"time":892781,"text":"Yes was the answer to the decoupling,"},{"time":895127,"text":"but also yes, we could replace\ncurrent fertilizer use"},{"time":898145,"text":"by a staggering 2.7 times."},{"time":902690,"text":"But what inspired me most\nabout the circular economy"},{"time":905250,"text":"was its ability to inspire young people."},{"time":908779,"text":"When young people see the economy\nthrough a circular lens,"},{"time":911914,"text":"they see brand new opportunities\non exactly the same horizon."},{"time":916488,"text":"They can use their creativity\nand knowledge"},{"time":919093,"text":"to rebuild the entire system,"},{"time":921480,"text":"and it's there for the taking right now,"},{"time":923593,"text":"and the faster we do this, the better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":926049,"text":"So could we achieve this\nin their lifetimes?"},{"time":929119,"text":"Is it actually possible?"},{"time":931255,"text":"I believe yes."},{"time":933105,"text":"When you look at the lifetime of\nmy great-grandfather, anything's possible."},{"time":937574,"text":"When he was born, there were only\n25 cars in the world;"},{"time":941310,"text":"they had only just been invented."},{"time":943740,"text":"When he was 14, we flew\nfor the first time in history."},{"time":947671,"text":"Now there are 100,000 charter flights"},{"time":950160,"text":"every single day."},{"time":952106,"text":"When he was 45, we built\nthe first computer."},{"time":956100,"text":"Many said it wouldn't catch on,\nbut it did, and just 20 years later"},{"time":959257,"text":"we turned it into a microchip"},{"time":961278,"text":"of which there will be thousands\nin this room here today."},{"time":965480,"text":"Ten years before he died,\nwe built the first mobile phone."},{"time":968359,"text":"It wasn't that mobile, to be fair,"},{"time":970333,"text":"but now it really is,"},{"time":972307,"text":"and as my great-grandfather\nleft this Earth, the Internet arrived."},{"time":976277,"text":"Now we can do anything,"},{"time":978390,"text":"but more importantly,"},{"time":979670,"text":"now we have a plan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":981985,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":984640,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}